    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-19T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="869"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/829: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chase</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-19T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 13th, 11 A.M.</p>
                <p>Obtain an official interview with Quiros, informing him of the attitude assumed
                    by the Government of the United States in telegram to San José dated February 9,
                    3 P.M., 1917.<note n="29" xml:id="d869fn29">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_307">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p. 307</ref>.</note> You
                    may say that the Government of the United States continues to feel as set forth
                    in that telegram that any person elected to the position of president of Costa
                    Rica in free, open elections held under the constitution of Costa Rica, violated
                    by Federico Tinoco, would appear to be [<hi rend="italic">have</hi>] good claim
                    to recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
